<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="570" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="570">
Derivation of name: The species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Germann" authorityYear="2021" box="[644,764,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Obhylius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arboricola">
<emphasis box="[644,764,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="570">arboricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the habitat of the new species in the canopy of an 
<taxonomicName box="[151,374,655,681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Aglaia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis box="[151,374,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="570">Aglaia macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tree in primary forest.
</paragraph>
